The paper deals with managing provenance data in scientific workflows, which is a common topic in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses the need for fine-tuning workflow parameters, which is a topic in Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Database (cs.DB) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the applicability of the proposed solution in different domains, which is a topic in Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the overhead of the proposed solution, which is a topic in Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
